Basic Linux Commands
ls //Lists all the files and folders available in the specified directory
mkdir //makes a directory
rmdir //removes a directory
touch // creates a file
cat> //creates and file and adds content given to it
cd //changes the directory
pwd //confirms the directory
cp //copies the files
rm //removes the files and directories
mv //moves the files and directoires
id //print user identity
groups //shows which groups user belongs to
passwd //change user password
who //find out who is logged into the systems
last //show history of logins into the system
chown //change file/directory ownership

